HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 248
BY REPRESENTATIVE MANDIE LANDRY
A RESOLUTION
To commend Michelle Woodfork on her election to the office of sheriff of Orleans Parish.
WHEREAS, it is with great pride that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana recognizes Michelle Woodfork for her outstanding service as a law
enforcement professional as she takes office as sheriff of Orleans Parish; and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Woodfork is a career police officer who has dedicated her life
to the protection and service of the city of New Orleans; her uncle, Warren Woodfork, was
the first Black chief of police in New Orleans; and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Woodfork previously served as interim superintendent of the
New Orleans Police Department, and during her tenure, the department enjoyed an extended
period of declines in violent crime; she also served under Orleans Parish District Attorney
Jason Williams prior to her election; and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Woodfork has pledged to build a culture where jail staff are
supported, respected, and equipped to do their jobs with professionalism, pride, and
confidence; she is committed to treating parish prisoners with dignity, fairness, and respect;
and
WHEREAS, Sheriff Woodfork aims to develop the Orleans Parish prison facilities
into centers for growth, rehabilitation, and education; and
WHEREAS, Orleans Parish Sheriff Michelle Woodfork is deserving of recognition
for her commitment to serving the citizens of the parish with integrity and leading with
accountability.
